    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, cut the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>in half</p><p>Cut 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> piece<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span>of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A3 paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>Tenderstem</strong> in the middle with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span>cold<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the Tenderstem to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until tender</p>",
